div.p:
No Body ever spoke before me, of a faithful Lover, but I still sigh'd, and thought of Damon: And ever, when they tell me Tales of Love, any soft pleasing Intercourses of an Amour;


Oh! with what Pleasure do I listen; and with Pleasure answer 'em, either with my Eyes, or Tongue—


That Lover may his Silvia warm;

But cannot, like my Damon, charm.
